      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to knock the consistency of OUR CRUNCH TIME NZ (4) who has placed in all four outings since winning at this circuit and distance. Produced yet another strong performance last time when he drew deep and raced parked but battled on bravely for third. Draws lower so can return to the winners' list. LUCCA NZ (11) made it back-to-back placings with another good effort last time at this circuit and distance, finishing second and just a head from the winner. If he gets the gaps from the second line he could break through. IMA FIVESTAR GENERAL NZ (1) has come from much wider barriers in each of this three starts since a spell. Much better served by the ace draw and should be at his peak for this. MASTER PUBLISHER NZ (6) has had little luck of late so could be going better than the recent form may suggest.",
